oai_dc:dc.dc:title: DESIGNING FOR PROPELLER ACTION IN HARBOURS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Hamill, G.A.
McGarvey, J.A.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: harbor
propeller action
propeller design
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The scour produced by the action of a ship's propeller is an increasing problem. There is a need for an accurate method of velocity perdition so that adequate steps can be taken to design suitable bed protection systems. The velocity characteristics of the jet produced by the rotating propeller are presented as an aid to the engineer.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 25 (1996): Proceedings of 25th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Orlando, Florida, 1996.
